patch.comment: Add `"node"` condition before `"import"` in the `"exports"` map so that Node.js uses the CJS output (which handles extensionless imports), while bundlers still use ESM via `"import"`. Fixes https://github.com/microsoft/rushstack/issues/5644.

minor.comment: Normalize package layout. CommonJS is now under `lib-commonjs`, DTS is now under `lib-dts`, and ESM is now under `lib-esm`. Imports to `lib` still work as before, handled by the `"exports"` field in `package.json`.
Normalize import of builtin modules to use the `node:` protocol.

patch.comment: Prefer `os.availableParallelism()` to `os.cpus().length`.
Include CHANGELOG.md in published releases again
Fix line endings in published package.
Update type-only imports to include the type modifier.
Update Webpack peerDependency to ~4.47.0.
Fix calculation of rendered module positions to properly reflect character codes, not raw bytes.
Fix async import compressor erroring when encountering unresolved dependencies.

minor.comment: Emit metadata about character position of rendered modules.

patch.comment: Change the peer dependency selector on `@types/node` to a wildcard (`*`).

minor.comment: Move the @types/node dependency to an optional peerDependency.

patch.comment: Rename from @rushstack/module-minifier-plugin.
Upgrade @types/webpack and add missing optional peer dependency.
Rename the "master" branch to "main".

minor.comment: Include plugin state in webpack hash calculations, such that updating the plugin options changes the compilation and chunk hashes.

Add support for `compressAsyncImports` flag. Modify `usePortableModules` option to use `module.identifier()` instead of `module.resource` so that loader configuration is accounted for during deduplication. Switch to overriding the render function on the JavaScript module template to deduplicate rendering across chunks.
Export a getIdentifier function for generating safe JavaScript identifiers.
Upgrade to terser 5.10.2, fix source maps in NoopMinifier
